<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-12-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="268" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d268">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Barrett</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-12-15"><hi rend="italic">December 15,
                                    1905</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 6.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of Mr.
                            Snyder’s No. 93, of the 7th ultimo, reporting the settlement of the
                            claim of Raymond and Sophie Smith by the payment of the amount claimed,
                            $1,500, in <hi rend="italic">vales de extranjeros.</hi></p>
                        <p>The Department approves Mr. Snyder’s action.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>